Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.91,0:03:29.03,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.75,0:03:33.38,Main,Laika,0,0,0,,You're home so late every \Nevening. You must be busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.90,0:03:36.89,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Sure you're not working too hard?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.89,0:03:38.45,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,No, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.45,0:03:42.72,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Even if I'm tired, I just need some \NNutri-Spirit, and I can keep fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.01,0:03:47.86,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,I've been using more of them \Nin a day recently, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.86,0:03:49.61,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,That's a bad thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.09,0:03:52.21,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Come home once the sun goes down.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.21,0:03:53.93,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,That's an order from your master!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.36,0:03:57.62,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,But there's a reason why \NI can't come home...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.74,0:04:00.89,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,A ghost?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.24,0:04:06.12,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Yes, apparently, a ghost has \Nbeen showing up in my factory.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.12,0:04:09.69,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,And now none of the locals \Nwant to work there...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.69,0:04:12.72,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,I can't get anyone at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.72,0:04:14.30,Main,Laika,0,0,0,,So that's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.50,0:04:16.96,Main,Falfa,0,0,0,,A ghost that just shows up in your factory?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.96,0:04:18.97,Main,Shalsha,0,0,0,,They call those "bound spirits."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.97,0:04:23.27,Main,Shalsha,0,0,0,,Scientifically, ghosts are \Nknown as "separated spirits."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.87,0:04:29.20,Main,Shalsha,0,0,0,,This type is most likely one that's \Nbound to the place where it died,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.20,0:04:30.61,Main,Shalsha,0,0,0,,so it can't leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.83,0:04:35.24,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,You mean it's the ghost of \Nsomeone who died there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.48,0:04:39.25,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Master, would you please get \Nrid of the ghost for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.78,0:04:40.73,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.12,0:04:44.54,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Uh, actually, I don't really \Nlike things like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.75,0:04:47.87,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Please! I need your help!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.87,0:04:53.44,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Otherwise, I'll have to run \Nthe entire factory by myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.08,0:04:55.36,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,True...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.66,0:05:04.09,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Oh, all right. I'll go \Ncheck it out tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.26,0:05:06.94,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Thank you so much, Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.18,0:05:08.45,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,But!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.45,0:05:10.84,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Only if I can bring a helper with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.64,0:05:12.88,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,A helper?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.77,0:05:15.72,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,What is this thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.00,0:05:18.85,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,It's summoning magic I learned a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.17,0:05:21.58,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,I don't know if it'll work or not, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.11,0:05:27.43,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Vosanosanon ujishidau veyani enrila.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.92,0:05:45.41,Main,Laika,0,0,0,,Nothing is happening...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.91,0:05:49.21,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,What in all Hell is going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.07,0:05:55.52,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,So cold... so cold... so cold... so cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.52,0:05:59.85,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,So cold... so cold... so cold... so cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.85,0:06:01.36,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Why'd you close the door?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.63,0:06:05.37,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Your pronunciation was a bit off,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.37,0:06:08.07,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,so I wasn't summoned into the \Nexact location you wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.35,0:06:12.03,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Why was your tub full of cold \Nwater in the morning, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.36,0:06:14.38,Main,Shalsha,0,0,0,,It's for watering our crops!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.38,0:06:15.37,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,It's eco-friendly!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.55,0:06:17.82,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Eco-friendly is all well and good, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.82,0:06:20.13,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Anyway, what was is it you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.19,0:06:24.92,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.24,0:06:28.45,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,You summoned me here just for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.45,0:06:30.04,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, really!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.04,0:06:33.56,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,But I had a feeling you'd be a big help.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.02,0:06:34.18,Narration - Top,SFX,0,0,0,,Scoot, scoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.96,0:06:35.49,Main,Falfa,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.06,0:06:37.88,Main,Falfa,0,0,0,,We knew you could...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.88,0:06:40.11,Main,Shalsha,0,0,0,,...do something about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.41,0:06:42.40,Narration - Top,SFX,0,0,0,,Squee!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.14,0:06:42.87,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Squee, indeed...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.47,0:06:48.67,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Well, it is true that I could \Ndo something about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.25,0:06:52.29,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,All right, take me to this factory.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.29,0:06:54.36,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,I'll pulverize this ghost!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.35,0:06:56.32,Narration - Top,SFX,0,0,0,,Lightbulb!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.62,0:06:58.69,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,The ghost only shows up at night,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.69,0:07:00.87,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,so could you wait until this evening?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.01,0:07:01.88,Narration - Top,SFX,0,0,0,,Snap!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.45,0:07:05.34,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,You should've waited until \Nevening to call me, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.09,0:07:08.59,Locales,Text,0,0,0,,The Town of Nascúte
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.60,0:07:10.84,Narration - Top,SFX,0,0,0,,Skree, skree, skree...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.71,0:07:14.17,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,I can imagine ghosts showing up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.50,0:07:17.64,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,That cat statue is super creepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.86,0:07:20.10,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Oh, I put that there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.10,0:07:21.39,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Isn't it cute?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.18,0:07:23.78,Italics,Azusa,0,0,0,,Halkara's tastes are kinda...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.13,0:07:27.69,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,What are you babbling about? Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.28,0:07:31.10,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,She really is a demon. No hesitation at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.10,0:07:33.28,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Looks like I chose the right helper.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.73,0:07:38.79,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Sure is dark in here...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.79,0:07:41.26,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,I really hope nothing shows up...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.26,0:07:44.93,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Don't be dumb. If nothing \Nshows up, why am I even here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.96,0:07:49.89,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Hey, Beelzebub...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.89,0:07:51.07,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.07,0:07:53.43,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Would you hold my hand? I'm scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.02,0:07:57.59,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,I feel as embarrassed as a little girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.88,0:08:00.49,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,but I suppose it can't hurt, so very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.81,0:08:05.89,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Master! Please hold my hand, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.89,0:08:11.45,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Halkara, where does this ghost show up?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.87,0:08:14.49,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,In the room up ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.76,0:08:17.79,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Then that room will be \Nthe focus of our search.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.12,0:08:22.13,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Um... Can we not go into \Nthat room? It scares me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.13,0:08:24.80,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,I agree! We should at \Nleast save it for last...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.80,0:08:25.71,Narration - Top,SFX,0,0,0,,Snap, snap!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.35,0:08:28.51,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Would you two cut it out?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.09,0:08:37.91,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Maybe we should call this off...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.81,0:08:41.65,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Agreed! There's nothing in this...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.39,0:08:46.24,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Oh, quiet down.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.24,0:08:49.46,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,You two are more of a \Nnuisance than that ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.86,0:08:51.83,Narration - Top,SFX,0,0,0,,Point!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.86,0:08:52.07,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Looks like it's over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.55,0:08:56.32,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,It {\i1}is{\i0} here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.32,0:08:58.28,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,I'm about to lose it in more ways than one!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.66,0:09:00.97,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,You two are making too much noise!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.97,0:09:03.00,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Just cool your heads for a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.29,0:09:07.43,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,It's only a ghost! The \Nspirit of a dead girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.43,0:09:08.84,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,What's scary about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.84,0:09:10.78,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's{\i0} what's scary about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.78,0:09:13.47,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,How are you so relaxed about this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.47,0:09:15.26,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,You're only scared because \Nyou can't see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.66,0:09:20.09,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Hey, girl's spirit! Show yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.09,0:09:21.59,Main,Both,0,0,0,,She's forcing it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.90,0:09:26.65,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,I am the high demon Beelzebub.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.65,0:09:27.95,Narration - Top,SFX,0,0,0,,Loom!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.19,0:09:30.43,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,I oversee the agriculture \Nof the land of demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.17,0:09:36.72,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,With my authority, I could turn this \Nplace into a horse manure shed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.72,0:09:38.66,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,That's low-key barbaric!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.66,0:09:41.62,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Please don't! This is my factory!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.41,0:09:47.12,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,If you don't want that, show yourself \Nby the time I count to ten!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.37,0:09:49.68,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,One...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.68,0:09:50.32,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Ten!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.32,0:09:52.12,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,You skipped a heck of a lot!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.57,0:09:55.65,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,There you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.92,0:10:01.42,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,I've got her! Give me some light!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.18,0:10:08.47,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Stop that! Hold still!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.19,0:10:12.68,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,Get your hands off me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.11,0:10:18.12,Eyecatch,Title,0,0,0,,I've Been Killing {\c&HE4AE06&}Slimes\N{\c&H313536&}for {\c&HE4AE06&}300 Years {\c&H313536&}and\N{\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H7600D0&}Maxed Out {\c&H313536&\3c&HFFFFFF&}My {\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H7600D0&}Level
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.89,0:10:21.10,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.10,0:10:22.87,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,I'm Rosalie.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.12,0:10:27.36,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,I'm the ghost of a girl who committed \Nsuicide in the house that once stood here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.81,0:10:28.50,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.77,0:10:29.71,Italics,Azusa,0,0,0,,Bad attitude...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.18,0:10:33.71,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Um... And why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.71,0:10:34.75,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,Why do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.14,0:10:37.39,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,This is the only place I {\i1}can{\i0} be!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.32,0:10:39.95,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,A few centuries ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.95,0:10:43.64,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,I was offered the chance to \Nmarry into a noble family.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.21,0:10:48.04,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,I had a reputation throughout the \Ntown for being pretty and polite,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.04,0:10:50.04,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,so I believed my parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.58,0:10:55.63,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,But my rotten father and mother \Nwere lying about everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.91,0:10:59.17,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,They intended to sell me \Noff for chump change!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.61,0:11:02.54,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,I see... You poor thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.54,0:11:04.50,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,Yeah, well, that's in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.50,0:11:07.16,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Um... I understand your story now,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.16,0:11:09.66,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,but were you really regarded as polite?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.91,0:11:13.07,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,In the centuries since I became a ghost...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.59,0:11:14.65,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,I went bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.98,0:11:18.19,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,That's certainly believable.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.19,0:11:22.60,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,I would expect an adolescent to change \Nlike that when betrayed by her parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.90,0:11:25.05,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,This is my turf!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.05,0:11:27.40,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,I don't want outsiders coming in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.40,0:11:29.40,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,Which is why I've defended \Nit all this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.08,0:11:33.48,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,And then you guys showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.81,0:11:34.72,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Rosalie...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.30,0:11:38.04,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,So what do you want to do from now on?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.44,0:11:40.49,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,What do I... want?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.62,0:11:42.50,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Ah, in that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.54,0:11:46.89,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,I can erase you in an instant \Nso you won't have to suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.89,0:11:48.54,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,None of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.71,0:11:49.98,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.98,0:11:54.55,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,I can help this ghost move on to the next \Nlife without leaving a trace behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.55,0:11:58.13,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,No way! I don't wanna disappear yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.61,0:12:00.10,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,I guess not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.60,0:12:03.96,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Okay, Rosalie, why don't \Nyou stay in this world?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.33,0:12:05.88,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,You mean it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.88,0:12:07.88,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,But won't I be a bother?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.88,0:12:09.18,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,What do you say, Halkara?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.57,0:12:12.10,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Um, you don't need to disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.10,0:12:14.19,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Can't you just go somewhere else?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.44,0:12:16.72,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,I've tried to move a few times,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.03,0:12:20.14,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,but I can't leave this building.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.14,0:12:22.91,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,I see. That's what Shalsha \Nwas talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.91,0:12:26.44,Main,Asusa,0,0,0,,She said bound spirits can't \Nleave the place where they died.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.66,0:12:28.36,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,I know a good way to resolve this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.60,0:12:29.52,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.52,0:12:32.25,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Demons have done extensive \Nresearch on spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.64,0:12:37.36,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,The latest research shows that if a \Nghost possesses a living human once,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.36,0:12:40.62,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,they will be able to go \Nwherever that human goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.80,0:12:42.31,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Possess?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.31,0:12:45.85,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,She would basically be using a \Nhuman as a vessel to relocate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.85,0:12:48.97,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,The best humans to possess are \Nthose with many weak points,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.31,0:12:53.35,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,those who are weak-willed and \Nreadily let others control them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.51,0:12:56.25,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.86,0:12:57.51,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Wha?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.98,0:12:58.61,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.99,0:13:00.74,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.89,0:13:03.75,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Please, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.94,0:13:05.69,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Just seeing a ghost scares me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.69,0:13:08.36,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,There's no way I can endure \Nhaving one inside me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.80,0:13:10.67,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,You'd be doing it for your factory.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.67,0:13:12.31,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Just bear with it for a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.31,0:13:15.85,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Master! How can you be so dismissive?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.82,0:13:20.14,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,Sorry, but I'm comin' in!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.14,0:13:22.96,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,No! I'll be traumatized!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.68,0:13:31.35,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,All right! I'm in!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.18,0:13:37.24,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,It feels weird to be in \Na physical body again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.64,0:13:40.44,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,These boobs are so heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.72,0:13:41.52,Narration - Top,SFX,0,0,0,,Boing! Boing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.90,0:13:43.31,Italics,Azusa,0,0,0,,That's your first thought, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.63,0:13:46.71,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,So, where are we taking her?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.93,0:13:50.61,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Well, we're running her out \Nfor our own reasons, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.61,0:13:53.16,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Rosalie, want to live at my house?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.16,0:13:55.63,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,Can I?! I won't be a bother?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.02,0:13:58.88,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,You were so unhappy in your previous \Nlife that you died, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.28,0:14:02.88,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Nothing bad will come of you \Nfinding happiness after death.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.31,0:14:04.54,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Come home with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.13,0:14:12.08,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,Let me call you "Sister"!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.08,0:14:15.50,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,I'll protect you if it kills me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.20,0:14:17.94,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,I mean, you're already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.52,0:14:21.47,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,What a smooth operator...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.47,0:14:23.82,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,A ghost operator, rather.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.00,0:14:26.31,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,Sister Laika!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.48,0:14:28.46,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,Sister's daughters!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.46,0:14:30.17,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,My name's Rosalie!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.17,0:14:31.49,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,Nice to meet all of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.65,0:14:36.44,Main,Laika,0,0,0,,It does feel quite strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.44,0:14:37.82,Main,Falfa,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.13,0:14:40.71,Main,Shalsha,0,0,0,,My first ghost... I'm so intrigued.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.12,0:14:47.42,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Well, I'm tired, so I'm going to bed now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.42,0:14:48.94,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Okay, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.16,0:14:50.18,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,Now, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.50,0:14:55.01,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,I will show you the real Rosalie!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.18,0:14:56.51,Main,Falfa,0,0,0,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.86,0:14:57.86,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,Here goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.11,0:15:03.97,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.39,0:15:09.95,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,Beelzebububububububububub!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.92,0:15:10.16,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Too many "bubs"!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.50,0:15:11.73,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,It's no use!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.73,0:15:14.83,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,It's like being stuck in \Na box! I can't get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.06,0:15:17.99,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,You two must have been \Nexceptionally compatible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.99,0:15:23.06,Main,Laika,0,0,0,,Um, this isn't going to cause any \Nirregularities in Halkara's body, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.28,0:15:27.03,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Obviously, if another's spirit \Nspends a full day in there,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.03,0:15:29.05,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,it will cause strain on her body.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.05,0:15:30.52,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Strain? How?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.52,0:15:32.49,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,In the worst case... she dies.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.49,0:15:33.64,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,That's {\i1}really{\i0} bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.29,0:15:38.51,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,I don't wanna kill someone \Nwho helped me out!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.51,0:15:41.96,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,If I have to do something that shameful...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.96,0:15:43.41,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,If it really comes to that...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.68,0:15:46.24,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,I have to die again to apologize!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.24,0:15:47.14,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,No, don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.14,0:15:51.19,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,If you do that now, Halkara \Nwill be the one to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.62,0:15:56.55,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,On that note, we're going to begin the \Nmission to separate Rosalie from Halkara.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.55,0:15:58.04,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Anyone have any good ideas?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.04,0:15:58.70,Main,Laika,0,0,0,,Me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.34,0:15:59.21,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Yes, Laika?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.21,0:16:02.68,Main,Laika,0,0,0,,Rosalie spoke of being \Nstuck in a box earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.89,0:16:05.71,Main,Laika,0,0,0,,When I have a cookie that's stuck in a box,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.71,0:16:07.33,Main,Laika,0,0,0,,the first thing I try is shaking it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.18,0:16:10.89,Narration - Top,SFX,0,0,0,,Vwoom, vwoom, vwoom...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.31,0:16:12.17,Narration - Top,SFX,0,0,0,,Sparkle!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.35,0:16:14.74,Main,Laika,0,0,0,,Then I try pounding on the back of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.78,0:16:21.62,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,Ow! Ow, ow, ow, ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.89,0:16:24.63,Main,Laika,0,0,0,,Otherwise... I break the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.90,0:16:26.91,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.12,0:16:28.36,Main,Falfa,0,0,0,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.36,0:16:31.57,Main,Falfa,0,0,0,,How about startling her, \Nlike when someone has the hiccups?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.18,0:16:38.14,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,S-Sister, where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.14,0:16:40.88,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,This intense wind concerns me...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.91,0:16:44.54,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.54,0:16:46.29,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,Where am I?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.48,0:16:50.48,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,I'm so high up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.38,0:16:56.23,Main,Laika,0,0,0,,I guess even ghosts don't like heights.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.36,0:16:58.86,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Well? Think you can leave her body now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.86,0:17:01.94,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,N-No! I'm just scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.18,0:17:04.59,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,I see... Guess we can't help that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.59,0:17:05.95,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Time for phase two, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.23,0:17:08.11,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,Huh? Phase two?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.79,0:17:14.04,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.78,0:17:31.54,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.82,0:17:32.69,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Did she come out?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.18,0:17:36.11,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,No, but I thought a few other \Nthings might come out...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.40,0:17:38.23,Main,Laika,0,0,0,,It didn't work?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.69,0:17:42.43,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,I guess we'll just have to try \Neverything we can think of.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.08,0:18:11.96,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,It's already noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.47,0:18:15.00,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,We're in trouble if we \Ndon't get her out soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.00,0:18:17.51,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Halkara's body might not \Nbe able to take much more.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.86,0:18:21.18,Main,Laika,0,0,0,,It looks like she's already reached \Nthat point in another sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.18,0:18:25.68,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,If only we could, at least, summon \NHalkara out of the body...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.10,0:18:27.86,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.86,0:18:32.37,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,If we put Rosalie to sleep right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.68,0:18:37.07,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,would Halkara's spirit come out?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.50,0:18:38.93,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.93,0:18:42.35,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,So we move that one in front \Nthat's getting in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.58,0:18:44.43,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,That just might work.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.43,0:18:47.54,Main,Laika,0,0,0,,But how do we put Rosalie to sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.54,0:18:48.60,Main,Hrosalie,0,0,0,,Help...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.56,0:18:51.14,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,Is this alcohol?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.69,0:18:54.30,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Halkara gets drunk on this all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.55,0:18:57.39,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,But I've never had alcohol before!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.85,0:19:00.05,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Your body is Halkara's, so you'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.23,0:19:02.73,Main,Laika,0,0,0,,It always puts her right to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.09,0:19:04.44,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,Okay, here I go!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.52,0:19:10.83,Main,HRosalie,0,0,0,,This is noth—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.44,0:19:14.18,Main,All,0,0,0,,It put her right out!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.91,0:19:18.65,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Huh? Why are we in Master's house?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.65,0:19:20.66,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Weren't we in my factory?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.66,0:19:22.40,Main,All,0,0,0,,It's Halkara!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.40,0:19:23.71,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,H-Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.96,0:19:27.47,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Okay! Now let's wake up \NRosalie and revive her!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.47,0:19:30.50,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Then she might come flying \Nout of Halkara's body!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.50,0:19:32.63,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,I know just how to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.63,0:19:34.39,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Leave this to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.08,0:19:35.92,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.86,0:19:41.00,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,The bath?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.19,0:19:44.33,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Beelzebub, how bold of you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.33,0:19:46.53,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm going to be bold, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.77,0:19:48.57,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,There you go!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.03,0:19:52.30,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,That's cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.75,0:19:55.63,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,There.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.63,0:19:56.56,Main,Laika,0,0,0,,She's out!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.56,0:19:57.53,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,It worked!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.27,0:20:01.35,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,All right! I made it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.54,0:20:05.53,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,S-So cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.52,0:20:08.41,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for all the trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.90,0:20:11.79,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,I'm going to be living here as of today!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.79,0:20:14.42,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,I'm Rosalie! I hope we can be friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.47,0:20:21.00,Main,Laika,0,0,0,,You really are a ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.00,0:20:22.48,Main,Falfa,0,0,0,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.48,0:20:23.55,Main,Shalsha,0,0,0,,I'm intrigued.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.08,0:20:26.80,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,I can't even see her as a different person.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.95,0:20:31.28,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,I'm impressed you figured out that \Ncold water would revive her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.28,0:20:35.68,Main,Beelzebub,0,0,0,,I remembered what happened when \Nyou summoned me yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.98,0:20:37.22,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,O-Oh, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.78,0:20:42.61,Main,Laika,0,0,0,,But I'm glad Halkara's factory \Nwill be able to operate now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.61,0:20:43.70,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.70,0:20:47.59,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,I'll just wait patiently until the \Nrumors about ghosts fade away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.85,0:20:50.43,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. It was all my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.43,0:20:53.59,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,Sister Halkara, at least \Nlet me pour you a drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.78,0:20:59.90,Main,Falfa,0,0,0,,Wow, that's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.90,0:21:04.00,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Hey, I know a way to get \Nrid of that rumor quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.72,0:21:09.30,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,Heya!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.30,0:21:12.52,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,I'm working at Sister Halkara's factory!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.52,0:21:13.98,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,My name's Rosalie!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.25,0:21:19.32,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,I'm a ghost, and I hope I can use \Nthis power to help all of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.81,0:21:22.54,Main,Woman,0,0,0,,That's remarkable!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.54,0:21:25.36,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,I guess not all ghosts are scary, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.36,0:21:26.99,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,She's cute, even!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.43,0:21:31.00,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,This is great.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.00,0:21:33.78,Main,Halkara,0,0,0,,It looks like the people of \Nthe town will accept her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.78,0:21:34.49,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.98,0:21:36.02,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,Sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.67,0:21:39.24,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,Thanks so much, Sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.24,0:21:42.73,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,I never knew I could find \Nhappiness after death!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.73,0:21:45.34,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,I'm so glad I died!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.71,0:21:47.79,Main,Azusa,0,0,0,,I'm not sure you should say {\i1}that{\i0}, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.19,0:21:49.34,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Hey, Rosalie!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.98,0:21:51.63,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Wipe my windows, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.63,0:21:53.25,Main,Woman,0,0,0,,And mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.25,0:21:54.83,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,You got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.83,0:21:57.54,Main,Rosalie,0,0,0,,I'll get each of your houses in turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.26,0:22:01.10,Italics,Azusa,0,0,0,,At this point,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.10,0:22:04.75,Italics,Azusa,0,0,0,,you might as well strive to be the most \Ncheerful ghost in the world.
